    {
      "type": "eq",
      "start": 140,
      "end": 155,
      "html": "<section class=\"slide eq\"><ul class=\"eq-lines\"><li id=\"imp8c9dao4s\" class=\" eq-item eq-title \" > Expansion of a Binomial </li><li id=\"imp8c9dao4t\" class=\" eq-item eq-math \" > $$ (a+b)^2 $$ </li><li id=\"imp8c9dao4u\" class=\" eq-item eq-math \" > $$ = (a+b)(a+b) $$ </li><li id=\"imp8c9dao4v\" class=\" eq-item eq-math \" > $$ = a(a+b) + b(a+b) $$ </li><li id=\"imp8c9dao4w\" class=\" eq-item eq-math \" > $$ = a^2 + ab + ab + b^2 $$ </li><li id=\"imp8c9dao4x\" class=\" eq-item eq-line \" > Two middle terms are identical. </li><li id=\"imp8c9dao4y\" class=\" eq-item eq-math \" > $$ = a^2 + 2ab + b^2 $$ </li><li id=\"imp8c9dao4z\" class=\" eq-item eq-line \" > This identity appears frequently in algebra. </li><li id=\"imp8c9dao50\" class=\" eq-item eq-math \" > $$ (x+y)^2 = x^2 + 2xy + y^2 $$ </li><li id=\"imp8c9dao51\" class=\" eq-item eq-line \" > Always verify expansions carefully. </li></ul><div class=\"eq-side-panel\"><div id=\"imp8c9dao4s-sp-1\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Expand the square step by step. </div><div id=\"imp8c9dao4s-sp-2\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Then combine like terms. </div><div id=\"imp8c9dao4t-sp-1\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > The bracket multiplies itself. </div><div id=\"imp8c9dao4u-sp-1\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" ><img src=\"box.webp\" /></div><div id=\"imp8c9dao4u-sp-2\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Area model of multiplication. </div><div id=\"imp8c9dao4v-sp-1\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Distribute both terms carefully. </div><div id=\"imp8c9dao4w-sp-1\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Every product is now visible. </div><div id=\"imp8c9dao4x-sp-1\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Both contain ab. </div><div id=\"imp8c9dao4y-sp-1\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Combine like terms. </div><div id=\"imp8c9dao4z-sp-1\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Used in simplification and factorization. </div><div id=\"imp8c9dao50-sp-1\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > The same pattern works for all variables. </div><div id=\"imp8c9dao51-sp-1\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Most algebra mistakes happen during expansion. </div></div></section>",
